# backend/ — FastAPI service (TDD-06)

Exposes the assistant and orchestrates **STT → agent → TTS**; holds session state;
REST + WebSocket. Design: `docs/tdd/TDD-06-Backend-API.md`; usage: `backend/README.md`.

## Run / test
```bash
cd backend
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate   # first time
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app.main:app --reload        # http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
pytest                               # end-to-end tests (offline stubs)
```

## Key conventions
- **Swappable services** in `app/services/` behind interfaces, so the API runs with
  no GPU/keys: `stt` (stub ↔ `WhisperSTT` via `LOAD_STT=true`, model
  `Amassu/whisper-small-darija`, **on by default**), `agent` (**LangGraph by
  default**, TDD-02, in `app/agent/` — LLM behind a provider interface, offline/no-key
  default; `AGENT_BACKEND=stub` is the explicit opt-out), `tts` (**local MMS-TTS by
  default**, TDD-05, on-CPU/no-key; `TTS_PROVIDER=stub` for silent test audio).
  Replace a stub **behind the same signature** — don't change the interface lightly
  (the frontend depends on it).
- **Knowledge base + RAG** (TDD-04) lives in `app/kb/` (per-`airport_id` YAML data
  pack + map-graph `directions` + `find_service` + ChromaDB/embedding `faq`). Backs
  the agent's KB tools and `POST /map`; built once in the service container
  (`state.py`) like the flight provider. `KB_RETRIEVER=chroma` (default — real
  embeddings, local, no key) or `keyword` (dep-free; tests set it via conftest).
  Build the store with `python -m app.kb.ingest --airport AUH`. New airport = drop
  `app/kb/data/<id>/`; never hard-code airport facts in code.
- **Config over code:** every provider/model/key comes from env (`app/config.py`),
  never a literal. See `.env.example`.
- **AirLabs is server-side only.** The flight tool calls AirLabs with
  `AIRLABS_API_KEY`; **strip the AirLabs `request`/meta block** (it echoes the key)
  before returning anything to the client. Cache responses (free tier = 1,000/mo).
- `flight_number`/`position` are **typed fields** on `/chat` & `/converse`, never
  parsed from audio. `airport_id` defaults to `AUH`.
- Update `app/schemas.py` (pydantic contracts) AND `docs/tdd/TDD-06` together when
  changing any request/response shape (consistency rule).
